Colgate-Palmolive (CL) vs. Avon Products (NYSE:AVP) Head-To-Head Comparison

					Posted by Anthony Sawyer on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 


Tweet












Colgate-Palmolive (NYSE: CL) and Avon Products (NYSE:AVP) are both consumer staples companies, but which is the better business? We will compare the two businesses based on the strength of their dividends, earnings, risk, analyst recommendations, valuation, institutional ownership and profitabiliy. 
Dividends


 Get Colgate-Palmolive Company alerts:



Colgate-Palmolive pays an annual dividend of $1.60 per share and has a dividend yield of 2.2%. Avon Products does not pay a dividend. Colgate-Palmolive pays out 59.5% of its earnings in the form of a dividend. Avon Products has increased its dividend for 53 consecutive years. 




Institutional & Insider Ownership
73.5% of Colgate-Palmolive shares are owned by institutional investors. Comparatively, 86.9% of Avon Products shares are owned by institutional investors. 1.0% of Colgate-Palmolive shares are owned by insiders. Comparatively, 1.3% of Avon Products shares are owned by insiders. Strong institutional ownership is an indication that large money managers, endowments and hedge funds believe a stock will outperform the market over the long term.
Risk & Volatility
Colgate-Palmolive has a beta of 0.8, meaning that its share price is 20% less volatile than the S&P 500. Comparatively, Avon Products has a beta of 1.83, meaning that its share price is 83% more volatile than the S&P 500. 
Analyst Recommendations
This is a summary of recent ratings and target prices for Colgate-Palmolive and Avon Products, as reported by MarketBeat.com. 



Sell Ratings
Hold Ratings
Buy Ratings
Strong Buy Ratings
